<li><a href="http://www.snowlionpub.com/samples/DZDL_Ch1.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.snowlionpub.com/samples/DZDL_Ch1.pdf" rel="nofollow">Dzogchen The Heart Essence of the Great Perfection, excerpt from Dalai Lama's book</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.rosecroixjournal.org/issues/2005/articles/vol2_41_62_pollock.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.rosecroixjournal.org/issues/2005/articles/vol2_41_62_pollock.pdf" rel="nofollow">Practices Supporting Dzogchen - The Great Perfection Of Tibetan Buddhism By Neal J. Pollock, M.A., N.D.</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/A%20-%20Tibetan%20Buddhism/Authors/Dudjom%20Rinpoche/The%20Dzogchen%20View%20of%20Tantra/Dzogchen%20View%20of%20Tantric%20Ngondro.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.abuddhistlibrary.com/Buddhism/A%20-%20Tibetan%20Buddhism/Authors/Dudjom%20Rinpoche/The%20Dzogchen%20View%20of%20Tantra/Dzogchen%20View%20of%20Tantric%20Ngondro.htm" rel="nofollow">Dzogchen View of Tantric Ngondro</a></li>
<li><a href="http://www.thebuddhadharma.com/issues/2005/spring/dudjom.html" class="external text" title="http://www.thebuddhadharma.com/issues/2005/spring/dudjom.html" rel="nofollow">Great Perfection in the Palm of Your Hand</a></li>
<li>Scheidegger, Daniel (2007). "Different Sets of Light-Channels in the Instruction Series of Rdzogs chen" in <i>Revue d’Etudes Tibétaines</i>. Source: <a href="http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/journals/ret/pdf/ret_12_03.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.digitalhimalaya.com/collections/journals/ret/pdf/ret_12_03.pdf" rel="nofollow">[3]</a> (accessed: Tuesday January 13, 2009)</li>
</ul>
